Education

Home Projects Experience

Hi, My name is Doina Colun, and I am a passionate software engineer with a deep-rooted love for solving complex problems with innovative solutions. I am thrilled to embark on my career in the industry after recently graduating from Ada Developers Academy with a certificate in Full Stack Web Development and Computer Science.
Throughout my studies, I have honed my skills in a variety of programming languages, including Python, JavaScript, Scala, and Java, and I have a strong foundation in data structures and algorithms. I am well-versed in agile software development methodologies, which have enabled me to work collaboratively with others to deliver high-quality projects on time.
During my time as a backend software engineer intern at Amazon, I gained valuable real-world experience, which has allowed me to develop a keen understanding of how to approach and solve challenging problems.
I have a particular interest in web development and have experience building websites using frameworks such as React. I take pride in creating dynamic, interactive interfaces that engage users and simplify their lives.
Outside of software engineering, I enjoy reading, cooking, playing sports to stay healthy, hiking, traveling, and exploring new technologies. I believe that constant learning and growth are crucial to stay relevant in the ever-changing field of software engineering.
I am eager to join a team that values innovation, collaboration, and growth. If you are interested in learning more about my experience and skills, please do not hesitate to reach out. I look forward to connecting with you!
